The paper focuses on improving semantic segmentation using deep convolutional neural networks, which is a topic within computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the theoretical and practical value of manipulating convolution-related operations, which falls under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The proposed methods involve dilated convolution, which is a common technique in neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper evaluates its approaches on various datasets, including Cityscapes and PASCAL VOC2012, which are commonly used in computer vision and natural language processing (cs.CL).
